 a covenant, and that the covenant will ask for patience when hurry claws at your heels.\", \"outcome\": \"Your work proceeds slower under the eyes of wardens and their careful rituals, but each reading carries the weight of accepted practice and cannot be easily denounced by rival guilds. At the Sluiceworks, Suri Yal grumbles at the ceremony but finds comfort in the way the warding cords steady the crews, and the bearings seem to sing more cleanly when the Order’s bell tone threads through the clatter. At Sternum Plaza, your whisper manifests as a clean band of frost that names only flows and oaths, not people, and Brother Halin quietly thanks you for keeping gossip hungry and thin. Lysa receives your notes with visible relief, noting that the deviations align across sacred and civic measures, and she underlines passages with a finger that trembles less than before. Some in the Ember Kiln Syndicate mutter that you have invited priests into matters of industry, but their complaints find little traction against the Order’s ledger of witness. You keep all promised rewards intact, and you gain a reputation for probity that will make some doors open on their hinges rather than on their locks.\"},\n        {\"id\": \"C2\", \"title\": \"Run a Grey Lantern Shadow Route\", \"text\": \"You slip from the Collegium by a side stair at lantern-dim and let your green-shutter light blink once toward Phosphor House, calling a truce-sign that only reflections know how to read. Within the tower, First Wick Tamsin Veil hears you out with a smile like a narrow bridge and offers routes that curl through the underways where rumor can be taught to walk in circles. Cor Yune lays a map on a pane of star-glass and traces the city’s rib-harmonics as if they were a contraband melody, promising that shutters and whispers will pinch closed behind you and keep Riverwarden eyes from prying. You make your tests between breaths and between shifts, reading gate-song when crews turn and frost-script w